ssh -R <bind_address>:<port>:<host>:<host_port> -l ubuntu localhost -p <puerto_servidor> -i C:\path-to.pem

[-L] address -> Specifies that the given port on the local (client) host is to be forwarded to the 
	given host and port on the remote side

[-R] address -> Specifies that the given port on the remote (server) host is to be forwarded to the 
	given host and port on the local side.

<bind_address> listen on all interfaces

ssh -R *:8080:localhost:80
ssh -R 0.0.0.0:8080:localhost:80

[-l] login name

ssh -R 0.0.0.0:5100:127.0.0.1:8080 -l ubuntu localhost -p 23403 -i C:\Users\user\Downloads\franky-stack.pem
ssh -R *:5100:127.0.0.1:8080 -l ubuntu localhost -p 23403 -i C:\Users\user\Downloads\franky-stack.pem

Configuracion
Por defecto OpenSSH solo permite conectarse a puertos "forwarded" desde el mismo server
Con la opcion "GatewayPorts" en el archivo "sshd_config" podemos controlar ese compotamiento:
yes -> permite conexiones de cualquiera. Si el servidor es publico
no -> evitar conexiones fuera del servidor
clientspecified -> el cliente puede especificar IPs de las cuales permitir conexiones

systemctl restart sshd
